<h4>Who is the target group for PGP Neighbors?</h4>
<p>A typical user of PGP Neighbors would be the owner of any of the 1.3 million+ public keys. The user is curious to see who
is in the user's immediate vicinity in the Web of Trust. The user wants an idea of how nested they are (how trusted they are), or
wants to verify that they are n degrees of separation from a famous person (a person with their own Wikipedia page). The user may check every
Monday for updates, because that's when niif's keyserver updates.</p>
